29/11/2010
TIRANA, Albania -- The country celebrated the 98th anniversary of its independence on Sunday (November 28th) with President Bamir Topi honouring all fallen patriots and those who fought for the nation and its flag. Celebrations were held in Vlora, where in 1912, the Albanian flag was raised to declare independence. Events marking the day were also held in Kosovo and Macedonia. (Vizion, Klan, Top News, Arta TV, Telegrafi - 28/11/10)
